					<h2>About Share Your Book</h2>
					<p>I am currently pursuing my AS / A-Levels in Mathematics, Biology, Physics and Chemistry at New English School, Kuwait &amp; aspire to pursue an Engineering degree in the United States of America. I am passionate about different subjects related to STEM (Science / Technology / Engineering &amp; Maths) as well as Geography &amp; languages.</p>
					<p>I've been an avid reader for as long as I can remember. As a child, the school library was my favorite place and I always end up reading books more advanced for my age/class. I think one thing that influences our reading is the environment we grow up in as children. My parents weren't avid readers, but have always supported my reading habits. Books allow me to explore new worlds, vastly different to our own. When I read, magic comes to life, I don’t see words on a page; I become the characters themselves, living in worlds with cultures both fictional and similar to our own. None of the books are stories I relate to, but those that open up my mind to new experiences, culture, narrative etc.</p>
					<p>For many years, I have found hard to get physical books that suit my tastes in Kuwait. With only a single big bookstore in Kuwait, I used to eagerly wait for my summer vacation in India so I could visit my local bookstore in Chandigarh, or with help from my father; buying books from Amazon India &amp; getting them to Kuwait by asking his friends coming back from there to bring my books.</p>
